Point of note: I am assuming that -5 is using centigrade when referring to the temperature. The metric system wasn't commonly used before 1960, and the UK didn't officially adopt the metric system until 1965. The degree symbol should also be after the number, rather than before, unless that is typical where you live. I tried to research this and so far most style guides recommend after. Here's my recommended re-write, if you are so inclined to update it:



Imagine, if you will: You shiver through a freezing night, only to be awoken to a 90° day.
